The paper deals with the problem of video-to-video synthesis, which involves learning a mapping function from an input source video to an output photorealistic video. This problem is related to computer vision (cs.CV) as it involves understanding the content of the input video and generating a corresponding output video. The proposed approach uses generative adversarial learning (GANs), which is a popular technique in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions experiments on multiple benchmarks, which suggests that it involves empirical evaluation and comparison of different methods, a common theme in multimedia (cs.MM) and graphics (cs.GR) research.
